title: Chris Isaak - 2016-01-30 - San Francisco
description:
Here is a very recent performance. Check my account for more bootlegs.

Please enjoy, share with friends and please seed :)


Chris Isaak
Super Bowl City
San Francisco, Ca
January 30,2016

Recorded by Daspyknows

Half way between stage and soundboard-dead center 
  
Schoeps MK41/NBox Platinum Tascam DR-2D 24 Bit 48K 

Processed using Soundforge 11, resample, to 16bit 44.1K
TLH to convert to Flac

Master 2016.07


No setlist has been posted.  I did the recording, I'll let someone else do the setlist.
 

I orginially planned to see Steel Pulse but the tour was cancelled due to David Hinds hospitalized
with pneumonia.  With that and the passing of Paul Kantner I knew I needed to see some music rather
than stay home.  With the weather looking OK I figured I would fight the masses and check out Chris
Isaak at Superbowl City in SF.  I took BART in and expected crowds.  The first thing that I thought
was how lucky I was not to be working in SF through all of this.  Walkthrough metal detectors and 
lots of security.  I soon realixed it was all for showand had no problem getting in.  I was able to 
get the perfect spot and it was crowded but not crazy at the music stage.  I arrived to some opening
band and went to find a spot to put on the gear.  Ended up setting up while waiting on line at a 
restaurant while grabbing food.  Got back for the soundcheck.  This was followed by annoying radio
personalities and a dj who played good music put enjoying ruining it.  After standing for 90 minutes
of that the Bay Bridge lights were turned back on which was cool.  Next was a fireworks display.  
Once the fireworks concluded Chris Isaak came on.  Solid show and good sound.  Aside from some talkers
it is a good recording.  Weather permitrting I will go back for the Alicia Keys set. 
  

Just the basic taper requests here and please no vitriol:
Don't be an ass by selling this or using it in a video that is sold
Don't modify the info file
Don't remaster and/or post on other sites that are not 100% free 
If shared keep info file intact but create a second file with any changes
Don't convert to lossy formats except for personal use
Do support the artists
